<p><a name="Etymology" id="Etymology"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Poverty&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Etymology">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Etymology</span></h2>
<p>The word "poverty" came from <a href="/wiki/Latin" title="Latin">Latin</a> <i>pauper</i> = "poor", via <a href="/wiki/Anglo-Norman_language" title="Anglo-Norman language">Anglo-Norman</a> povert.</p>
<p><a name="Measuring_poverty" id="Measuring_poverty"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Poverty&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Measuring poverty">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Measuring poverty</span></h2>
<div style="float:right;clear:right;border:none;width:220px;margin:0 0 1em 1em;padding:0">
